o someone openly and up-front, someone in an authoritative position,'' the <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> official said. Several indirect overtures from <LOCATION> Iran </LOCATION> were received in the past and did not produce a substantive diplomatic dialogue between <LOCATION> Washington </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Tehran </LOCATION>. However, the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> is able to talk indirectly to the Iranian government through a number of foreign countries, including <LOCATION> Algeria </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Japan </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Germany </LOCATION>.
