<HEAD>Trucker Arrested After Accidents on Interstates</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: UPDATES throughout with two seriously injured, 25 vehicles
hit, citizens surrounding man, other details.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>SAN ANTONIO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A semi-truck driver was arrested today after he raced through morning rush hour at speeds up to 90 mph, ramming his rig into at least 25 other vehicles, police said. At least two people were seriously injured. `` People said he was just pushing people off the road,'' a police dispatcher said. Sheriff's deputies chased the Peterbilt tractor-trailer rig for about 30 miles before he pulled into a rest area on Interstate 35 near <LOCATION> Devine </LOCATION>, southwest of <LOCATION> San </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Antonio </LOCATION>. A group of citizens there surrounded the driver until officers arrested him. Police found a small amount of cocaine in his rig, said <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Public </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Safety </ORGANIZATION> trooper <PERSON> Marshall </PERSON> <PERSON> Milikien </PERSON>. The man was taken to the <LOCATION> Medina </LOCATION> <LOCATION> County </LOCATION> jail in <LOCATION> Hondo </LOCATION>. The first hit-and-run incident was reported shortly after 8 a.m. on Interstate 10 near Comfort in <LOCATION> Kendall </LOCATION> <LOCATION> County </LOCATION>, about 40 miles northwest of <LOCATION> San </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Antonio </LOCATION>, said <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Public </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Safety </ORGANIZATION> trooper <PERSON> Alvin </PERSON> <PERSON> Schacht </PERSON>. The trucker sideswiped a vehicle driven by <PERSON> Robert </PERSON> <PERSON> Etlinger </PERSON> of <LOCATION> Boerne </LOCATION>, who was run off the road. When the rig did n't stop, <PERSON> Etlinger </PERSON> gave chase but was unable to catch him, <PERSON> Schacht </PERSON> said. The trucker `` was running between 85 and 90 and he -LRB- Etlinger -RRB- could n't catch him,'' <PERSON> Schacht </PERSON> said. The truck eventually hit at least 18 cars in <LOCATION> San </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Antonio </LOCATION> and seven elsewhere, police said. Many vehicles were sideswiped and rear-ended. At least two people were seriously injured, said Department of Public Safety trooper <PERSON> Marshall </PERSON> <PERSON> Milikien </PERSON>.
