 <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> Gov. <PERSON> Mario </PERSON> <PERSON> Cuomo </PERSON> today denied a request for clemency from the woman convicted in the 1980 murder of <LOCATION> Scarsdale </LOCATION> Diet author Dr. <PERSON> Herman </PERSON> <PERSON> Tarnower </PERSON>. <PERSON> Jean </PERSON> <PERSON> Harris </PERSON>, 65, is serving 15 years to life for the slaying of her lover. Friends and relatives of <PERSON> Harris </PERSON>, a former headmistress at an exclusive <LOCATION> Virginia </LOCATION> girls' school, had mounted a petition appeal campaign on her behalf. They said as many as 10,000 letters had been sent to <PERSON> Cuomo </PERSON> and that they had delivered petitions containing 25,000 signatures seeking clemency for her. Neither <PERSON> Harris </PERSON>' lawyer nor family members could be reached immediately for comment today. Other than to say clemency for <PERSON> Harris </PERSON> had been denied, <PERSON> Cuomo </PERSON> spokeswoman <PERSON> Anne </PERSON> <PERSON> Crowley </PERSON> declined to discuss the matter. <PERSON> Harris </PERSON> has always maintained she meant to kill herself and not <PERSON> Tarnower </PERSON> on March 10, 1980, when she drove to his house just north of <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> <LOCATION> City </LOCATION> from her home at the <ORGANIZATION> Madeira </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Girls </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> School </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> McLean </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Va </LOCATION>. Upset because he had taken up with a younger woman, <PERSON> Harris </PERSON> wound up shooting <PERSON> Tarnower </PERSON> four times. She said the shooting was an accident. The governor today granted clemency to two state prison inmates, <PERSON> Bernice </PERSON> <PERSON> Lane </PERSON> and <PERSON> Emilio </PERSON> <PERSON> Vasgonez </PERSON>, who were serving 15 years-to-life sentences on drug sale charges. In a statement issued with his clemencies, <PERSON> Cuomo 