ionage, or those who, in `` cumulation of offenses, committed homicide, robbery and caused public danger.'' The revolt began Oct. 23, 1956, with mass demonstrations for a new government amd demands that Soviet troops leave <LOCATION> Hungary </LOCATION>. On Nov. 4, 200,000 Soviet troops and 2,500 tanks struck at <LOCATION> Budapest </LOCATION> to quell the uprising
