<HEAD>Austrian Catholics Choose New Archbishop, Criticize Vatican</HEAD>
<DATELINE>VIENNA, Austria (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Roman Catholic leaders announced the selection of conservative <PERSON> Georg </PERSON> <PERSON> Eder </PERSON> as <LOCATION> Salzburg </LOCATION>'s new archbishop Friday but complained of bias in the <LOCATION> Vatican </LOCATION>'s list of candidates for the post. In an official statement carried by the <ORGANIZATION> Catholic </ORGANIZATION> news agency <ORGANIZATION> Kathpress </ORGANIZATION>, the 12-member <ORGANIZATION> Salzburg </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Cathedral </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Chapter </ORGANIZATION> said <PERSON> Eder </PERSON> accepted the body's appointment Thursday. It must now be formally made by Pope <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> Paul </PERSON> <PERSON> II </PERSON>. The announcement comes at a time when the <ORGANIZATION> Catholic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Church </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> Austria </LOCATION> is suffering from widening divisions over the appointment of conservative bishops and with contentious issues, including the pope's stand on birth control and women's role in the Church. <PERSON> Eder </PERSON> is known as a conservative priest who says Mass in Latin with his back to the congregation. The Second Vatican Council in the 1960s called for use of a new Mass in the vernacular with the priest facing the faithful. The <LOCATION> Salzburg </LOCATION> chapter said it broke the traditional secrecy surrounding such appointments because of advance media criticism of the choice of yet another conservative for a top church post. <PERSON> Eder </PERSON> was considered by commentators as the least conservative of three candidates put forward for selection by local church leaders. An estimated 260,000 believers have left the church in the past eight years. According to a critical Catholic journal, 30,917 left the church in 1987 alone. The local church leaders also criticized the <LOCATION> Vatican </LOCATION>'s three candidates, saying the list was biased. `` The Cathedral Chapter had to recognize that the selection of candidates for this triple proposal was not taken in such a balanced fashion as could be expected,'' they said in a joint statement. The statement said they had `` exhausted every available possibility'' to make the <LOCATION> Vatican </LOCATION> aware of `` the needs of the diocese and the views of the area.'' They said they had sent a letter on the issue to the <LOCATION> Vatican </LOCATION>. The appointments of conservative <PERSON> Hans </PERSON> <PERSON> Hermann </PERSON> <PERSON> Groer </PERSON> as archbishop of <LOCATION> Vienna </LOCATION> in September 1986 and of ultra-conservative <PERSON> Kurt </PERSON> <PERSON> Krenn </PERSON> as assistant bishop of <LOCATION> Vienna </LOCATION> five months later triggered open protest and division in <LOCATION> Austria </LOCATION>'s <ORGANIZATION> Catholic </ORGANIZATION> ranks. In the <LOCATION> Vatican </LOCATION> <LOCATION> City </LOCATION> on Friday, the pope nominated five new auxiliary bishops in <LOCATION> Hungary </LOCATION> and another in the tiny central African country of <LOCATION> Rwanda </LOCATION>. The pope nominated the Revs. <PERSON> Vilmos </PERSON> <PERSON> Dekany </PERSON> and <PERSON> Asztrik </PERSON> <PERSON> Varszeghi </PERSON> to posts in <LOCATION> Esztergom </LOCATION>; the Rev. <PERSON> Istvan </PERSON> <PERSON> Acs </PERSON> in <PERSON> Eger </PERSON>; the Rev. <PERSON> Mihaly </PERSON> <PERSON> Mayer </PERSON> in Pecs; the Rev. <PERSON> Nandor </PERSON> <PERSON> Takacs </PERSON> in <LOCATION> Szekesfehervar </LOCATION>; and the Rev. <PERSON> Felicien </PERSON> <PERSON> Muvara </PERSON> in <LOCATION> Butare </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Rwanda </LOCATION>.
