ppeal of 14 former members of <PERSON> Bishop </PERSON>'s New Jewel Movement and the revolutionary government who were convicted in <PERSON> Bishop </PERSON>'s murder. Since then, the hearings had taken up a total of 27 days. Proceedings had been adjourned until Jan. 28. It was expected that a judgment would be handed down by summer. <PERSON> Haynes </PERSON>' death means this timetable will have to be revised to find a replacement for <PERSON> Haynes </PERSON> and to give the new president time to study the court records of the murder trial.
