<HEAD>ABC Movie Tells Story of Young AIDS Victim's Fight To Attend School</HEAD>
<NOTE>With LaserPhoto</NOTE>
<BYLINE>By JERRY BUCK</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>AP Television Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 In the <ORGANIZATION> ABC </ORGANIZATION> movie `` The Ryan White Story,'' look for a scene in a hospital in which the young AIDS victim talks to a friend named <LOCATION> Chad </LOCATION>. <PERSON> Chad </PERSON> is played by <PERSON> Ryan </PERSON> <PERSON> White </PERSON>, the <LOCATION> Indiana </LOCATION> youngster who took on fear, ignorance and the establishment in his determination to go to school despite being diagnosed as having the deadly acquired immune deficiency syndrome. <PERSON> Chad </PERSON> is a friend who died of AIDS. <PERSON> Lukas </PERSON> <PERSON> Haas </PERSON> -LRB- `` Witness'' -RRB- plays <PERSON> Ryan </PERSON>. Producer <PERSON> Linda </PERSON> <PERSON> Otto </PERSON> said it was director <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> Herzfeld </PERSON>'s idea to have <PERSON> Ryan </PERSON> play <LOCATION> Chad </LOCATION>. `` <PERSON> Ryan </PERSON> was a natural,'' she said. `` He just understands. He has a sixth sense. I loved being around him. He's enriched my life. `` He's just turned 17, he drives a car. No one quite understands why he's fine, but he is. <PERSON> Ryan </PERSON> has determined to do well and have a good life. The lesson of the movie is overcoming adversity. It's not about AIDS, although that's what he has. `` I did n't want to make a movie about a boy dying of AIDS. I wanted to make a movie about a kid living with AIDS. Every movie you see about AIDS, the person dies. Even if <PERSON> Ryan </PERSON> had died I would n't have him die in the movie But I knew he would n't die. I knew he'd hang in there. At the end of the movie, which <ORGANIZATION> ABC </ORGANIZATION> broadcasts Monday, there is another look at <PERSON> Ryan </PERSON>, plus his mother, <PERSON> Jeanne </PERSON>, and his sister, <PERSON> Andrea </PERSON>. <PERSON> Judith </PERSON> <PERSON> Light </PERSON> plays <PERSON> Ryan </PERSON>'s mother, <PERSON> Nikki </PERSON> <PERSON> Cox </PERSON> his sister. <PERSON> George </PERSON> <PERSON> C. </PERSON> <PERSON> Sco