</TEXT>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
 A year-end search for bargains among blue-chip issues propelled stock prices to a broad rally Thursday. The Dow Jones average of 30 industrials climbed 16.25 points to close at 2,182.68 _ less than a point below its 1988 closing high of 2,183.50, reached Oct. 21. The dollar ended lower against most major currencies in thin, volatile trading. Bond prices and yields were fairly stable. Coffee futures prices surged to their highest levels in more than two years; gold, silver and energy futures retreated; grains and soybeans were mixed; livestock and meat futures were mixed; and stock-index futures advanced.
